snippet.title: GOAT BLOOD FRY | Traditional Goat Blood Recipe Cooking In Village | Goat Blood Gravy with Intestine
snippet.description:
Today in our village, We cook our village's traditional goat blood recipe by making blood gravy and blood fry. We call this recipe as "Raththa Koottu" and "Raththa Poriyal". We add some goat internal parts to goat blood gravy, such as the liver, lungs, and intestine.

Finally, we enjoy the food with our favourite muttun curry! The taste is delicious!

snippet.description:
In this video, Madan Gowri speaks about the recently released Malayalam blockbuster movie, Manjummel Boys, and the real incident in which the movie was inspired and made. He says that a gang of 11 boys from Kerala have travelled to Tamil Nadu's Kodaikanal for a trip. As a part of the trip, those boys went to Guna Caves, which are located in Kodaikanal, got trapped in the caves, and were finally rescued from there. This Manjummel Boys movie is based on this real-life incident. Guna Cave was named after the Guna movie, in which Kamal Hassan was theÂ protagonist.

snippet.title: Mrs. Nita Ambani's Performance to Vishwambhari Stuti For Anant & Radhika's Prewedding Celebration
snippet.description:
Celebrating tradition and invoking the divine, Mrs. Nita Ambani presents a stirring performance to the Vishwambhari Stuti, a sacred hymn dedicated to Maa Ambe, the embodiment of power and strength. She has been hearing this hymn since her childhood during every Navratri. Tonight, as she performs with grace and devotion, she seeks Maa Ambe's blessings for Anant and Radhika's journey of togetherness. She also dedicates her performance to her granddaughters, Aadiya Shakti and Veda, and to all young girls, who are a symbol of feminine energy. 

Credits:
Director & Director of Choreography: Vaibhavi Merchant.
Creative Director: Shruti Merchant. 
Music Directors/Composers: Ajay-Atul
Singer: Shreya Ghoshal
Director of Photography: Anil Mehta 
Production Design: Amrita Mahal
Mrs. Nita Ambani's Costume: Manish Malhotra
Dancers' Costume: Ashley Rebello

#AnantRadhika
#ARPreWeddingCelebrations #NitaMukeshAmbaniCulturalCentre
#SwadeshOnline

snippet.title: Thankamani | Trailer | Dileep | Ratheesh Reghunandan | Super Good Films | Saina Music | Iffaar Media
snippet.description:
Thankamani is an upcoming Indian Malayalam-language crime thriller film written and directed by Ratheesh Reghunandan and Produced by R B Choudhry under the banner of Super good films in association with Iffaar Media Raaffi Mathirra. The film stars Dileep and is based on a real-life incident that occurred in Thankamany in October 1986. Thankamani Music Rights has been acquired by Saina Music.

snippet.title: #Exclusive | Anant Ambani And Rahul Kanwal Take a Tour of Vantara Kingdom Elephant Kitchen
snippet.description:
#anantambani #rahulkanwal #anantambaniengagement #mukeshambani #vantara #RadhikaMerchant #NitaAmbani 
Step into the fascinating world of Vantara Kingdom's Elephant Kitchen with Rahul Kanwal, Executive Director of Business Today, and Anant Ambani, Director of Reliance Industries Limited, in a special edition of 'Jab We Met'. Embark on an exclusive tour as Anant Ambani and Rahul Kanwal explore the intricacies of the Elephant Kitchen, where the majestic residents of Vantara Kingdom are nourished. Witness firsthand as Rahul Kanwal delves into the unique culinary offerings for the elephants, discovering surprising treats that are not only savored by these gentle giants but also enjoyed by humans. From tasting delectable ladoos to refreshing watermelon juice, indulging in wholesome khichdi, and savoring popcorn treats meant for the elephants, Rahul Kanwal immerses himself in the culinary delights of Vantara Kingdom's Elephant Kitchen. Experience the joy of this extraordinary encounter as Anant Ambani and Rahul Kanwal unravel the secrets of this special sanctuary.
-----------------------
Thank You for watching! Do not forget to Like | Comment | Share

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS! SUPERB FODEN BRACE INSPIRES CITY TO DERBY TRIUMPH | Man City 3-1 Man United
snippet.description:
Phil Foden scored two stunning goals as City recovered from a goal down to beat Manchester United 3-1.

City had fallen behind to a thunderous Marcus Rashford goal on eight minutes - against the run of play - and spent the next 50 minutes or so trying to find a way past a resolute United back-line.

But Foden levelled on 56 minutes with a screamer into the top corner from 20 yards, then scored a delightful second ten minutes from the end of normal time.

snippet.description:

Khumar Episode 30 [Eng Sub] Digitally Presented by Happilac Paints - Feroze Khan - Neelam Muneer - 2nd March 2024 - Har Pal Geo

Khumar Digitally Presented by Happilac Paints

Khumar is a timeless love story that delves into the challenges arising from societal class differences and the negativity that stems from them. Khumar explores the complexities of love in the face of societal expectations and challenges. Faiz and Hareem, two individuals from different backgrounds, find their lives connected by destiny.

Faiz, born into an affluent family, contrasts sharply with Hareem, who hails from a
lower-middle-class background. Despite their differences, fate weaves their paths together. Hareem, diligently working to make ends meet amid her brother Rufi's educational needs and her mother's medical expenses, faces numerous hurdles. In the midst of her struggles, Faiz, a friend of Rufi's, silently supports them financially and even gets work for Hareem, albeit discreetly.

Hareem's family doesn't know that Faiz loves her, leading to a one-sided love affair. Faiz's love for Hareem remains a secret, but his mother disapproves of his association with Hareem's family due to the significant class difference. But fate decides to play its tune, and an unexpected event turns the lives of Faiz and Hareem upside down.

What was this surprising turn of events that changed everything for Faiz and Hareem? Will the gap in their social status keep them apart? Can Faiz convince his mother to accept Hareem? If they marry, can they create a happy life together despite their different backgrounds and mindsets?

Hareem, diligently working to make ends meet amid her brother Rufi's educational needs and her mother's medical expenses, faces numerous hurdles. In the midst of her struggles, Faiz, a friend of Rufi's, silently supports them financially and even gets work for Hareem, albeit discreetly.

Hareem's family doesn't know that Faiz loves her, leading to a one-sided love affair. Faiz's love for Hareem remains a secret, but his mother disapproves of his association with Hareem's family due to the significant class difference. But fate decides to play its tune, and an unexpected event turns the lives of Faiz and Hareem upside down.

What was this surprising turn of events that changed everything for Faiz and Hareem? Will the gap in their social status keep them apart? Can Faiz convince his mother to accept Hareem? If they marry, can they create a happy life together despite their different backgrounds and mindsets?

Popatlal experiences a surreal moment as he hallucinates a version of himself, engaging in a conversation about his marriage concerns. This video captures the essence of the unforgettable night that had the audience on their feet, cheering for more. Get ready to be amazed by the dynamic duo and experience the magic they create together. Don't miss out on this epic performance that showcases the best of Diljit Dosanjh and the charisma of Anant Ambani.

Letâ€™s see how to make healthy vegetable ghavan and chutney today. My daughter has specially asked me to make something light and full of veggies for breakfast. So, here I am with the recipe. Now a days, kids are cauntious what they eat specially during exam period. So in a way, this will helpful to you too. This is a very easy and simple recipe. As it has lot many veggies, it is healthy too!! This recipe doesnâ€™t need lot many ingredients. You can make it from very few basic ingredients those are readily available in your kitchen. It looks nice and tempting and tastes just awesome. 

Ingredients:
Ghavan
â€¢ 4~5 tbsp Rice flour
â€¢ Salt to taste
â€¢ Water as needed
â€¢ Finely chopped Spinach
â€¢ Grated Carrot
â€¢ 1/2 Lemon juice
â€¢ Oil 
Chutney
â€¢ 1 tbsp roasted Chana dal
â€¢ 4~5 grated fresh Coconut
â€¢ Coriander leaves
â€¢ 2~3 Green chilies
â€¢ 1 small piece of Ginger
â€¢ Salt to taste
â€¢ Sugar to taste
â€¢ Water as needed
â€¢ 1/2 tsp Oil
â€¢ 1 tsp Mustard seeds
â€¢ 1 tsp Cumin seeds
â€¢ A pinch of Hing
â€¢ Curry leaves

Method:
Ghavan
â€¢ Mix rice flour and salt well together and add a little water at a time to make runny batter. 
â€¢ Wash spinach and carrot really good and grate the carrot. 
â€¢ Chop the spinach finely. 
â€¢ You can add veggies of your choice like finely chopped onion, capsicum or tomato etc. 
â€¢ Add the veggies into the batter and add lemon juice. 
â€¢ Mix everything well together and batter for ghavan is ready. 
â€¢ Heat up a pan on medium heat and grease it well with oil. 
â€¢ Mix the batter well once and make ghavan. Start pouring the batter along the edge of the pan and
  finish off at the center. 
â€¢ Cover and cook the ghavan for about a minute. 
â€¢ Remove the lid and when lower side is roasted well, flip the ghavan over. 
â€¢ Roast well from other side too. 
â€¢ When the ghavan is roasted well from both sides, talk it off on a wore rack. Ghavan is ready. 
â€¢ Serve it with chutney.  
Chutney
â€¢ Blend roasted chana dal, fresh coconut, coriander leaves, green chilies, ginger, salt and sugar well 
  together dry first. Avoid use of water while blending now. 
â€¢ Add water and blend it well again. 
â€¢ Transfer the chutney into a bowl. 
â€¢ Heat up oil in a pan and add mustard seeds. 
â€¢ When mustard pop up turn on the gas and add cumin seeds, hing and curry leaves. 
â€¢ Mix well and add the tadka into the chutney. 
â€¢ Mix well and chutney is ready.

snippet.description:
Thanks for watching Har Pal Geo. Please click here https://bit.ly/3rCBCYN to Subscribe and hit the bell icon to enjoy Top Pakistani Dramas and satisfy all your entertainment needs. Do you know Har Pal Geo is now available in the US? Share the News. Spread the word.

Khumar Episode 29 [Eng Sub] Digitally Presented by Happilac Paints - Feroze Khan - Neelam Muneer - 1st March 2024 - Har Pal Geo

Khumar Digitally Presented by Happilac Paints

Khumar is a timeless love story that delves into the challenges arising from societal class differences and the negativity that stems from them. Khumar explores the complexities of love in the face of societal expectations and challenges. Faiz and Hareem, two individuals from different backgrounds, find their lives connected by destiny.

Faiz, born into an affluent family, contrasts sharply with Hareem, who hails from a
lower-middle-class background. Despite their differences, fate weaves their paths together. Hareem, diligently working to make ends meet amid her brother Rufi's educational needs and her mother's medical expenses, faces numerous hurdles. In the midst of her struggles, Faiz, a friend of Rufi's, silently supports them financially and even gets work for Hareem, albeit discreetly.

Hareem's family doesn't know that Faiz loves her, leading to a one-sided love affair. Faiz's love for Hareem remains a secret, but his mother disapproves of his association with Hareem's family due to the significant class difference. But fate decides to play its tune, and an unexpected event turns the lives of Faiz and Hareem upside down.

What was this surprising turn of events that changed everything for Faiz and Hareem? Will the gap in their social status keep them apart? Can Faiz convince his mother to accept Hareem? If they marry, can they create a happy life together despite their different backgrounds and mindsets?

7th Sky Entertainment Presentation 
Producers: Abdullah Kadwani & Asad Qureshi 
Writer: Maha Malik
Director: Ali Faizan

Cast:
Feroze Khan as Faiz
Neelam Muneer as Hareem
Hina Bayat as Kehkasha Begum
Asma Abbas as Durdana
Behroz Sabzwari as Sheikh Furqan
Zainab Qayoom as Dil Araa
Shehryar Zaidi as Taufeeq
Adnan Samad as Nasir
Sheherzade Peerzada as Hamna  
Minsa Malik as Laiba 
Kinza Malik as Atiya
Mehmood Akhtar as Zaawar  
Agha Mustafa as Rayyan  
Hamzah Tariq as Rufi
Ayesha Rajpoot as Shagufta
Mizna Waqas as Husna
Sohail Masood as Mirza Sahab
Birjees Farooqui as Salma

Shiddat Episode 07 [Eng Sub] - Muneeb Butt - Anmol Baloch - Digitally Presented by PEL - 4th March 2024 - HAR PAL GEO

Shiddat Digitally Presented by PEL

Asra, a beautiful and cherished young woman, has led a life filled with love and care from her family. In contrast, Sultan, a determined and charismatic perfectionist, overcomes the challenges of his troubled childhood to consistently achieve his desires.

Despite their stark personality differences, Asra falls in love with Sultan. However, after they marry, Asra realizes that Sultan is not the ideal man she had envisioned. To please him, she sacrifices her desires and undergoes a significant transformation.

This revelation becomes the catalyst for an unending series of problems between them. The journey through marital life becomes a complex maze as Asra and Sultan attempt to navigate challenges, each trying to mold the other according to their own will and preference.

Will Asra and Sultan change for each other, or will the growing list of problems between them persist? When Asra discovers the reality about Sultan, how will she react? Is Sultan contemplating leaving Asra? Can love overcome all obstacles, or are some differences too profound to bridge?
